cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal verification techniques for Petri nets, which is a well-known formalism in the field of logic and automata theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the construction of a symbolic reachability graph, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper describes a Java tool-set for automating the graph construction algorithm. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with the verification of real-time systems, which is a common concern in software engineering. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper deals with modeling and analyzing real-time systems, which is a topic of interest in the field of control systems.
